parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire valve stem can cause tire blowouts, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Tire blowouts
especially at the sidewall
with minimal tread wear and low mileage
often resulting in sudden loss of air pressure and potential loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to go to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down
the emergency brake is needed to stop the vehicle.
